Definition courte: % of time that a cell is available to accept traffic.
Definition longue: NR Cell Availability (NR_CA) is defined as the percentage of time  within a given measurement period  that a cell or measurement area is available to accept traffic. It does not include the time when the RBS is not available due to Planned Downtime due to  for example  restarts. Cell Availability is measured over a defined set of cells -usually a cluster or market area. KPI is on NRCellDU level. The CA is measured using statistical counters and/or RBS logfiles. The CA metric can be further broken down to reflect cell outage times for planned (manual) or unplanned (auto) events.
